# 7Planner API – Frontend Integration Guide

This document explains how the frontend should interact with the 7Planner backend API.

---

# Base URL

All routes are prefixed with `/v1`.

Development:

```
http://localhost:5000/v1
```

Production:

```
https://api.7-planner.com/v1
```

---

# Authentication

Authentication uses **JWT Bearer tokens** for protected routes and **HttpOnly cookies** for refresh tokens.

After login or register, store the access token and include it in every protected request:

```
Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN
```

The refresh token is automatically managed via an HttpOnly cookie (`refresh_token`).

---

# Auth Endpoints

## Register

```
POST /v1/auth/register
```

Request:

```json
{
  "name": "John",
  "surname": "Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "timezone": "Europe/Istanbul"
}
```

Response `201`:

```json
{
  "message": "User successfully created",
  "accessToken": "JWT_TOKEN"
}
```

> Sets `refresh_token` HttpOnly cookie.

---

## Login

```
POST /v1/auth/login
```

Request:

```json
{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
```

Response `200`:

```json
{
  "message": "Successfully logged in",
  "accessToken": "JWT_TOKEN"
}
```

> Sets `refresh_token` HttpOnly cookie. Rate limited per email and IP.

---

## Refresh Token

```
POST /v1/auth/refresh
```

No request body. Uses the `refresh_token` cookie automatically.

Response `200`:

```json
{
  "message": "Token refreshed successfully",
  "accessToken": "NEW_JWT_TOKEN"
}
```

> Call this endpoint when the access token expires (401 response).

---

## Forgot Password

```
POST /v1/auth/forgot-password
```

Request:

```json
{
  "email": "john@example.com"
}
```

Response `200`:

```json
{
  "message": "If the email exists, a password reset link has been sent."
}
```

> Always returns 200 to prevent email enumeration. Reset link is valid for 15 minutes.

---

## Reset Password

```
POST /v1/auth/reset-password
```

Request:

```json
{
  "token": "RESET_TOKEN_FROM_EMAIL",
  "newPassword": "newpassword123",
  "confirmPassword": "newpassword123"
}
```

Response `200`:

```json
{
  "message": "Password successfully changed"
}
```

> Invalidates all active sessions after reset.

