# Task Templates

Templates define tasks. A task can be one-shot (has `dueDate`) or repeatable (has `repeatUnit`).

---

## Create Template

```
POST /v1/u/templates
```

One-shot example:

```json
{
  "title": "Pay electricity bill",
  "description": "Before the deadline",
  "dueDate": "2026-03-15"
}
```

Repeatable example:

```json
{
  "title": "Go to gym",
  "description": "Workout session",
  "repeatUnit": "day",
  "repeatInterval": 1,
  "startDate": "2026-03-12"
}
```

Repeat unit options: `day`, `week`, `month`

Response `201`:

```json
{
  "message": "Task template successfully created"
}
```

---

## Get Templates

```
GET /v1/u/templates
```

Returns all active and inactive templates for the current user.

---

## Get Template Detail

```
GET /v1/u/templates/:id
```

---

## Update Template

```
PATCH /v1/u/templates/:id
```

Updatable fields:

```
title, description, dueDate, repeatUnit, repeatInterval, startDate
```

---

## Set Template Status

```
PATCH /v1/u/templates/:id/status
```

Request:

```json
{
  "isActive": false
}
```

