# Basic Application Flow

1. User registers or logs in → receives `accessToken`, cookie is set
2. Store `accessToken` in memory
3. Attach `Authorization: Bearer <token>` to every protected request
4. On `401` response → call `POST /v1/auth/refresh` to get a new token
5. Fetch current user (`GET /v1/u/me`)
6. Fetch today's tasks (`GET /v1/u/tasks/today`)
7. Register push token on app launch (`POST /v1/u/notifications/tokens`)
8. On logout → call `POST /v1/u/auth/logout` and clear stored token

